g.text: SIMD Function Dispatch: Dynamic ISA Selection

ol.li: Detection Overhead: Executed exactly once per process lifetime via library constructors.
Indirection Penalty: Modern branch predictors (BTB) alias the VTable pointer after ~3 calls, reducing overhead to < 2 cycles.
Binary Bloat: "Fat binaries" contain all compiled kernels; only the optimal path is resident in the instruction cache.
